  <div class="instr-block">
    <h3>Part A — 20 Flashcards (5 min)</h3>
    <p>Prepare 20 flashcards mixing multiplication facts, short division, and simple fraction recognition — all within your child's confident ability (e.g. 6×7, 48÷6, "what is half of 36?"). Show one by one at steady pace. Child calls out the answer as fast as possible. <strong>Neutral face throughout — no feedback at all.</strong></p>
    <p>After card 20, immediately switch format — say the next three questions as word stories rather than showing cards. Watch whether engagement visibly changes with the format switch.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="instr-block">
    <h3>Part B — Make a Pattern (5 min)</h3>
    <p>Give your child paper and a pencil. Say:</p>
    <div class="script">"Make up a pattern — numbers, shapes, letters, anything — with a hidden rule. Don't tell me the rule. I'll try to guess it."</div>
    <p>Give them up to 3 minutes. Say nothing. If they ask "what kind?" say only: <em>"Any kind you like."</em></p>
  </div>
